    public interface Proxy
extends Service, ProxyTypes, com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService

    • Method Detail

      • test

        Proxy.TestInvocation test(java.lang.String host,
                          java.lang.String protocol,
                          ProxyTypes.Config config)
        Tests a proxy configuration by testing the connection to the proxy server and test host. This method was added in vSphere API 6.7.

        Invocation Result:
        Status of proxy settings.

        Operation Errors:
        Error - Generic error.

        Parameters:
        host - A hostname, IPv4 or Ipv6 address.
        protocol - Protocol whose proxy is to be tested.
        config - Proxy configuration to test.
        Returns:
        instance of Proxy.TestInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described test operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.

      • set

        Proxy.SetInvocation set(java.lang.String protocol,
                        ProxyTypes.Config config)
        Configures which proxy server to use for the specified protocol. This operation sets environment variables for using proxy. In order for this configuration to take effect a logout / service restart is required. This method was added in vSphere API 6.7.

        Operation Errors:
        Error - Generic error.

        Parameters:
        protocol - The protocol for which proxy should be set.
        config - Proxy configuration for the specific protocol.
        Returns:
        instance of Proxy.SetInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described set operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
